            . On the 30th of June, between three and four in the afternoon, I was passing down Holbourn; at the end of <placeName id="t17670715-39-crimeloc243">Fetter-lane</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17670715-39-crimeloc243" type="placeName" value="Fetter-lane"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17670715-39-crimeloc243" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17670715-39-off241 t17670715-39-crimeloc243"></join> I felt a jerk at my pocket, I turned round, and saw the prisoner going down Fetter-lane with something<xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="176707150032"></xptr> red in his hand; I found my handkerchief was gone; I pursued him, he took into a house about three or four doors down the lane, I followed him, and upon charging him, he either gave me the handkerchief out of his pocket, or I took it out, I do not know which (produced in court, marked L. and a figure of 7;) the house he ran into happened to be the constable's house; he begged and prayed for forgiveness, and went on his knees.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's defence.</p>
               <p>I was going down Holbourn, and picked up the handkerchief near the pastrycook's; when he asked for it, I said he was welcome to it.</p>
